>I have a 72 van with what I believe to be a 1700 engine.
>On my van it is missing the timing marks or the timing mark piece that bolts
>to the outer crankcase.

The pulley should have a mark as depicted here:

http://type2.com/library/electrip/timemark.htm

A new timing scale can be bought from Bus Boys for < $5.

http://www.bus-boys.com/aircoolsystem.html

Someone on the list once gave me some good advice and recommended that I paint the letters white so they are easier to read.

>Can anyone offer any suggestions as to fing TDC withoout those marks?

On my distributor there is a very small notch on the rim (after you take off the cap) that will show you TDC for #1 when the rotor is aligned with the notch.

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/DizzyNotch.jpg
